cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is the most likely category as the paper introduces a new notion of winning cores in parity games and develops an algorithm for solving parity games based on this notion. 
- cs.DS (Computer Science and Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents a deterministic polynomial-time under-approximation algorithm for solving parity games. 
- cs.LO (Computer Science and Logic in Computer Science) is another possible category as the paper deals with formal logic and game theory. 
- cs.AI (Computer Science and Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper presents an algorithm for solving games, which is a common topic in AI. 
- cs.PL (Computer Science and Programming Languages) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses properties of winning cores, which could be relevant to programming language semantics.
